1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:20,000
At an international summer school, I struggled to follow lectures and conversations in English. I wanted to improve, but had little dedicated study time.

2
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:40,000
I also kept waiting for AI tools. AIterval turns that unused waiting time into one focused English listening sprint.

3
00:00:40,000 --> 00:01:02,000
I send my normal request. AIterval observes only generation-state controls, never my prompt or response. Then one short question appears.

4
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:15,000
When the AI finishes, audio stops immediately. I return to work, and only real recovered seconds are added to progress.

5
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:38,000
For an upcoming lecture, I enter its title, abstract, terms, level, focus, locale, and duration, then explicitly request generation.

6
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:50,000
GPT-5.6 uses the Responses API and Structured Outputs. The pack is validated before the extension stores and schedules it.

7
00:01:50,000 --> 00:02:15,000
The dashboard shows recovered time, weak skills, and reviews—without a punitive streak. The 132 built-in exercises still need no API key.

8
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:40,000
I made the product and privacy decisions. In one primary Codex task, Codex helped turn them into adapters, a state machine, schemas, tests, deployment, and evidence.

9
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:52,000
AIterval does not ask busy people to find more time. It turns time they already lose into a learning habit.
